/ Layout - Susy
%section#susy.element-group
  %h1.section-title Layout - Susy
  %p.intro
    :markdown
      Default Variables for setting up a [Susy](http://susy.oddbird.net/) grid

      See the [Susy Reference](http://susy.oddbird.net/guides/reference/) for details.
  %div#total-columns.element
    %h2.element-title
      %a.permalink{:href => "#total-columns"}
        total-columns
    .extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - The number of Columns in your default Grid Layout.
          - Unitless number.
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $total-columns: 12;
  %div#column-width.element
    %h2.element-title
      %a.permalink{:href => "#column-width"}
        column-width
    .extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - The width of a single Column in your Grid.
          - Length in any unit of measurement (em, px, %, etc).
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $column-width: 6em;
  %div#gutter-width.element
    %h2.element-title
      %a.permalink{:href => "#gutter-width"}
        gutter-width
    .extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - The space between Columns.
          - Units must match $column-width.
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $gutter-width: 2em;
  %div#grid-padding.element
    %h2.element-title
      %a.permalink{:href => "#grid-padding"}
        grid-padding
    .extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - Padding on the left and right of a Grid Container.
          - Units must match $column-width.
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          $grid-padding: $gutter-width;
  %div#Example.element
    %h2.element-title
      %a.permalink{:href => "#Example"}
        Example
    .extendable-source
      .comment
        :markdown
          - Build the grid by calling susy mixins on DOM elements
      %pre.scss
        :preserve
          #container {
            @include container;
            @if $show-grid == true {
              @include susy-grid-background;
            }
            @elseif $show-baseline == true {
              @include baseline-grid-background;
            }
          }
          .main {
            @include span-columns(8);
          }
          .side {
            @include span-columns(4 omega);
          }

